research and idea generation; (d) researchers are suspicious and confused about
open access, but less so if produced by a traditional publisher; (e) there was a
uniformity of perceptions/behaviour of researchers irrespective of differences in
subject, country, and age; (f) although some early career researchers behave the
same as their more senior colleagues this is because of a fear of the system: they
